# POLIS — Editing Conventions

## Code style

- Everything is global in one `<script>`. Names are intentionally **terse**
  (`S` = state, `G` = grid, `c` = cell, `cx` = canvas ctx). Match it.
- Comments explain **why / balance intent**, not what. Preserve them; they
  encode hard-won tuning. Do not add narration comments.
- Plain ES (no TypeScript, no modules, no JSX). Don't introduce a build step,
  bundler, or npm dependency — the single-file, zero-dependency nature is a
  core feature (it must run by just opening the file).

## After changing the map or cell data, refresh derived state

The simulation caches a lot. When you mutate `map`, cell types, or networks:

```js
recomputeNets();     // power + water flood-fill (only if connectivity changed)
recomputeFields();   // pollution / crime / land value / coverage
dirty = true;        // force the next frame to redraw (renderer is decoupled)
```

Forgetting `dirty = true` is the usual cause of "my change doesn't show up":
the frame governor skips redraws when idle.

## Adding a new building / tile type — checklist

Tile types are serialized **by array index**, so order is load-bearing:

- [ ] Append the id to **`TYPE_IDS`** (~6509) — **never reorder or remove**
      existing entries, or every saved city breaks.
- [ ] Add a display name in `NAMES` (~5434).
- [ ] Register it in the relevant trait tables so systems pick it up:
      `ZONE`/`SVC`/`ROADTYPE`/`WALKTYPE`/`CONDUCT`, plus `UPKEEP`, and
      `CAP`/`PLANT`/`WSRC`/`LEIS`/`FOOT` as applicable.
- [ ] Add it to the `TOOLS` catalog (~858) with cost `c`, icon, group.
- [ ] Give it a draw path in `render()` / a `draw*` function.
- [ ] Handle placement in `place()` (~1445) if it needs special rules.

## Save format

`makeSave()` (~6557) / `loadSave()` (~6566) encode the city as
`TLV3.<base64(JSON)>`: per-cell `[typeIndex, lv, dev, mergeFlag]` plus `S`
fields. If you change the cell payload shape, **bump the version prefix**
(`TLV3`→`TLV4`) and keep `loadSave` able to read older codes (it already
branches on `TLV2`/`TLV3` stride). Persistent slots go through `store`
(artifact API → localStorage fallback); autosave fires monthly.

## Balance tuning

Gameplay numbers live in **named tables**, not scattered literals — tune there:
`UPKEEP`, `CAP`, `PLANT`, `WSRC`, `LEIS`, `ROAD_CAP`, `DIFF`, `LOAN_OFFERS`,
and the growth thresholds inside `simTick()`. Prefer adjusting a table constant
over editing per-tile logic.

## Testing changes

Open `index.html` (or `python3 -m http.server`) and verify in-browser. Useful
quick checks: load a demo with `loadDemo(EXAMPLE_CITY)`, watch the stats charts
modal, and confirm save→reload round-trips after any `TYPE_IDS`/save change.
The game is **mobile-first** (pointer events, pinch-zoom, DPR-aware canvas) —
sanity-check touch interactions when touching input or layout.
